<subSubSection pageNumber="768" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="768">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="768">Note:</emphasis>
Nordborg (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="768">Opera Bot.</emphasis>
16: 98. 1967) chose a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
for this name because 1127.1 (LINN), although original material, was unidentifiable as to subspecies. A 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
cannot be maintained when original material exists (Art. 9.17) so, despite the deficiencies of the material, Purohit &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Panigrahi’s">Panigrahi's</normalizedToken>
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
choice has priority. However, under Art. 9.8, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Nordborg’s">Nordborg's</normalizedToken>
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
choice can be accepted as an 
<typeStatus>epitype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
